author: The Current
description:
Watch Gillian Welch and David Rawlings play "Hashtag"
Support The Current: https://support.mpr.org/youtube  

On Friday, Nov. 8, Gillian Welch and David Rawlings’ 10th studio album, Woodland, was nominated for a Grammy Award in the category of Best Folk Album, and the lead track, “Empty Trainload of Sky,” received a nomination for Best Americana Performance. 

While in St. Paul for two nights of concerts at the Fitzgerald Theater, Welch and Rawlings walked over to The Current where Radio Heartland host and producer Mike Pengra welcomed them, along with bassist Paul Kowert, for a studio session, where they performed "Hashtag" and two others from "Woodland."

Gillian Welch & David Rawlings’ 2024 album, "Woodland," is available on  @aconyrecords .

Musicians
Gillian Welch – guitar, vocals
David Rawlings – guitar, vocals
Paul Kowert – bass 

Credits
Guests –  @gillianwelch  and  @davidrawlings

title: Gillian Welch and David Rawlings perform "Hashtag" at The Current

To celebrate The Current’s 20th Anniversary, The Current’s Live Sessions Vault unlocks never-before-seen live performance videos of bands and artists who have played in our iconic studio. 

Watch to see the full three-song session of Bombino, featuring previously unreleased footage, from when he visited The Current studio back in 2016.

Songs Performed 
00:00:00 Tihegren/Emé
00:05:41 Akhar Zaman (This Moment)
00:10:02 Iyat Ninhay/Jaugar (A Great Desert I Saw)
